   And thatвАЩs it: call вОХDLX to get the solution(s).  In general all
problems that can be solved by вОХDLX contain 3 steps:

   вАҐ translate the problem into a constraints matrix B,
   вАҐ ZвЖРвОХDLX B, and
   вАҐ translate the result Z back into the problem domain.

   Another application of вОХDLX is solving sudokus.  The constraints
matrix is a little more complicated, but the principle is the same.  GNU
APL is shipped with two workspaces: sudoku.apl (which solves sudokus
without using вОХDLX) and sudoku_DLX.apl (which solves sudokus using
вОХDLX).


