2.26 вОХFIO - File I/O Functions
==============================

As of GNU APL 1.6, the native function FILE_IO has been replaced by the
system function вОХFIO. вОХFIO normally takes a numeric axis argument which
selects one of many different functions, most of which are contained in
the standard C library.  The arguments for these functions are usually
the same as the corresponding C functions and the man page for each
function describes the meaning of the arguments.

   For example, вОХFIO[3] corresponds to fopen() and вАЩman fopenвАЩ explains
what fopen does (opening a file).

   Calling вОХFIO monadically without an axis and with an empty right
argument shows a list of all functions provided by вОХFIO:

