2.27 вОХFFT - Fast Fourier Transform
==================================

For those interested in signal processing and the like, GNU APL provides
вОХFFT:

   The monadic form вОХFFT B is a shortcut for the dyadic form 0 вОХFFT B.
It computes the FFT of complex or real B without applying a window
function.

   The dyadic form A вОХFFT B provides more control over what вОХFFT
computes.  A is an integer scalar which falls into one of three ranges.

   The first range from ¬ѓ15 to ¬ѓ10 does not compute an FFT, but returns
the result of multiplying B with one of several window functions, that
are frequently used in the context of FFTs.  The result has same shape
as B and can be used for analyzing or troubleshooting FFTs:

   вАҐ A=¬ѓ10: no FFT, return the Hann window applied to B
   вАҐ A=¬ѓ11: no FFT, return the Hamming window applied to B
   вАҐ A=¬ѓ12: no FFT, return the Blackman window applied to B
   вАҐ A=¬ѓ13: no FFT, return the Blackman-Harris window applied to B
   вАҐ A=¬ѓ14: no FFT, return the Blackman-Nuttal window applied to B
   вАҐ A=¬ѓ15: no FFT, return the Flat-Top window applied to B

   The second range around 0 contains the computation of the forward and
inverse FFTs:

   вАҐ 0 вОХFFT B returns the "normal" (aka.  forward) FFT of the numeric
     array B.
   вАҐ ¬ѓ1 вОХFFT B returns the inverse FFT of the numeric array B.

   The third range from 10 to 15 corresponds to the first range and
first multiplies B with a window function and then computes the FFT:

   вАҐ A=10: FFT(B √Ч Hann window)
   вАҐ A=11: FFT(B √Ч Hamming window)
   вАҐ A=12: FFT(B √Ч Blackman window)
   вАҐ A=13: FFT(B √Ч Blackman-Harris window)
   вАҐ A=14: FFT(B √Ч Blackman-Nuttal window)
   вАҐ A=15: FFT(B √Ч Flat-Top window)

   вНівНіB can be 1 (one-dimensional FFT, the most common case) or more.
The implementation of вОХFFT uses libfftw3, aka.  "The fastest Fourier
Transform in the West."  GNU APL checks the presence of libfftw3 when it
is ./configureвАЩd.  If libfftw3 is present then вОХFFT will hopefully
return the expected result; if not then a DOMAIN ERROR will be raised
when вОХFFT is used.

   вОХFFT honors the presence of /etc/fftw/wisdom (see man fftw-wisdom) to
speed up the computations performed by вОХFFT. Creating /etc/fftw/wisdom
will take a few hours, though, so that creating it will not pay off for
most mortals.


