2.29 вОХJSON - JSON Parsing
=========================

GNU APL provides вОХJSON for decoding and encoding JSON strings and files.
A (valid) JSON string is mapped to an APL value as follows:

   вАҐ JSON value вЖРвЖТ structured or non-structured APL value
   вАҐ JSON number вЖРвЖТ APL number
   вАҐ JSON string вЖРвЖТ APL string
   вАҐ JSON literal вЖРвЖТ enclosed APL string (one of either вКВвАЩnullвАЩ,
     вКВвАЩtrueвАЩ, or вКВвАЩfalseвАЩ )
   вАҐ JSON array вЖРвЖТ APL vector
   вАҐ JSON object вЖРвЖТ structured APL value (associative array)

2.29.1 Monadic вОХJSON
--------------------

ZвЖРвОХJSON B converts the string B into an APL value according to the
mapping above.  If that fails then command )MORE provides information
about the error and where in B the error was detected.

2.29.2 Dyadic вОХJSON
-------------------

ZвЖРA вОХJSON B performs one of the following conversions:

   вАҐ ZвЖР0 вОХJSON B is the same as monadic ZвЖРвОХJSON B.

   вАҐ ZвЖР1 вОХJSON B is like ZвЖР0 вОХXML B, except that B is not the JSON
     string itself but the name of a file from which a JSON string is
     read.

   вАҐ ZвЖР2 вОХJSON B is the inverse of ZвЖР0 вОХXML B. It converts an APL value
     to a JSON string.

   вАҐ ZвЖР3 вОХJSON B is like 2 вОХJSON B, except that the member names (keys)
     of all JSON objects are sorted alphabetically.  That is of little
     use (but costs performance) if Z is not displayed but processed
     further, but it could help troubleshooting when Z is displayed and
     the number of keys in Z is large.


