2.30 вОХMAP - Map Value
=====================

вОХMAP changes the ravel items of its right argument according to a
mapping table provided as its left argument.  Let ZвЖРA вОХMAP B.

   The left argument A of ZвЖРA вОХMAP B shall be a N√Ч2 matrix.  Each
2-element row of A, say A[J;], specifies a separate mapping A[J;1] вЖТ
A[J;2].  The result Z has the same shape as the right argument B. The
items Z[...]  of their result are constructed from their corresponding
items B[...]  in B as follows:

   вАҐ if B[...]  вЙ° A[J;1] for some J then Z[...]  is A[J;2].

   вАҐ otherwise B[...]  is different from all A[1;J] and then Z[...]  is
     B[...]

   In other words, Z is B, but with items of B found in A[;1] replaced
by their mapped item A[;2].

   In practice the left argument A is frequently created from a literal
APL value such as 5 2вНівАЩeEwWaAzZ92вАЩ in the example below.  To simplify
these cases, A вОХMAP B also accepts a vector instead of a N√Ч2 matrix:

   A вОХMAP B вЖРвЖТ ((N 2)вНіA) вОХMAP B if (2√ЧN) вЖРвЖТ вНіA

   Examples:

      вНЭ the map A
      вКҐAвЖР5 2вНі'eEwWaAzZ92'
eE    вНЭ map 'e' вЖТ 'E'
wW    вНЭ map 'w' вЖТ 'W'
aA    вНЭ map 'a' вЖТ 'A'
zZ    вНЭ map 'z' вЖТ 'Z'
92    вНЭ map '9' вЖТ '2'

      вНЭ the value B being mapped
      вКҐBвЖР'Halloween'
Halloween

      вНЭ the result of A вОХMAP B
      A вОХMAP B
HAlloWEEn

      AвЖР'eEwWaAzZ92'   вНЭ vector A instead of N√Ч2 matrix
      A вОХMAP B
HAlloWEEn


   NOTES:
   вАҐ The keys of the mapping A (i.e.  the elements in column A[;1]) must
     be unique.  If they are not then the mapping is ambiguous and a
     DOMAIN ERROR is raised.

   вАҐ Nested items in B: if an item of B is nested, then it is either
     equal to some (also nested) key, say A[N;1], (in that case it is
     being mapped to A[N;2] in the result), or it is different from all
     keys in A[;1] (and in that case the corresponding item in the
     result is the item in B.

   вАҐ Nested items in A: if a key, say A[N;1], is nested and matches an
     equal (hence also nested) item in B, then the corresponding item in
     the result will be A[N;2] (which may or may not be nested).  If a
     (nested or not nested) key A[N;1] is equal to an item in B, then
     the corresponding item in the result will be nested if A[N;2] is
     nested.  If, for some N, the depths of A[N;1] and A[N;2] differ,
     then depths of B and A вОХMAP B may differ as well.  That is, вОХMAP
     conserves the shape of B, but not necessarily the depth of B.

   вАҐ By default the mapping of B is non-recursive, i.e.  the top-level
     items of B are compared with the top-level keys A[;1], and nested
     keys and items of B are handled as described above.

     Sometimes, however, it is desirable to recursively descend into the
     nested sub-values of B (though never of A). This can be achieved by
     enclosing A as shown in the examples below.

      AвЖР5 2вНі'eEwWaAzZ92'
      BвЖР'Hal' 'low' 'een'   вНЭ nested B
      4 вОХCR A вОХMAP B        вНЭ non-recursive (none of the keys in A[;1] matches)
вФПвЖТвФБвФБвФБвФБвФБвФБвФБвФБвФБвФБвФБвФБвФБвФБвФБвФБвФУ
вФГвФПвЖТвФБвФБвФУ вФПвЖТвФБвФБвФУ вФПвЖТвФБвФБвФУвФГ
