2.31 вОХMX - Matrix/Statistics
============================

вОХMX was kindly contributed by Henrik Moller

   вОХMX[x] is a system function that provides a collection of matrix and
statistical operations such as covariance, eigensystems, and so on,
along with random number generation in several statistical
distributions.  Particular operations are selected through the use of
the axis specifier x:

            вОХMX[1] B       (monadic) Determinant
        (A) вОХMX[2] B       (nomadic) Cross product
          A вОХMX[3] B       (dyadic)  Vector angle
            вОХMX[4] B       (monadic) Eigenvector
            вОХMX[5] B       (monadic) Eigenvalue
            вОХMX[6] B       (monadic) Ident
            вОХMX[7] B       (monadic) Rotation matrix
          A вОХMX[8] B       (dyadic)  Homogeneous transform
            вОХMX[9] B       (monadic) Norm
        (A) вОХMX[10] B      (nomadic) Randoms
        (A) вОХMX[11] B      (nomadic) Covariance
          A вОХMX[12] B      (dyadic)  Histogram
          A вОХMX[13] B      (dyadic)  Print
            вОХMX[14] B      (monadic) Set RNG seed

   (These may by shown by entering вОХMX вАЭ or вОХMX[0]0 on the APL command
line.)  In the function list above, A indicates a mandatory left
argument, while (A) indicates an optional left argument.  The right
argument B of вОХMX[X] is always mandatory.

2.31.1 Determinant
------------------

The determinant operation, вОХMX[1], is monadic and is valid only for
numeric arguments (real or complex) where вНівНіB = 2 and (1вЖСвНіB) = (¬ѓ1вЖСвНіB)
(i.e.  a square matrix).  For Example:

      mx[1] 3 3вНі5 3 1 9 7j2 6 2 8 4j5
