2.34 вОХPS - Print Style
======================

вОХPS is an integer vector that currently (read: as of SVN 982) contains
two integers which control some details of how APL values are printed.
The default value of вОХPS is 0 0.  вОХPS is a session variable which
survives the *)LOAD*ing of workspaces.

   вОХPS[1] = 0: print rational quotients as normal floating point numbers
(digits, fractional point, possibly an exponent).

   вОХPS[1] = 1: print rational quotients as Numerator√ЈDenominator.

   Note: вОХPS[1] has no effect if rational numbers were not
./configureвАЩd.

   вОХPS[2] = 0: no "boxing" of APL values

   вОХPS[2] > 0: "boxing" of APL values according to вОХPS[2].

   Setting вОХPS[2] has the same effect as the debug command ]BOXING and
uses the same values.

   Note: For compatibility with older workspaces, assigning a single
value to вОХPS assigns that value to вОХPS[2] and sets вОХPS[1] to 0.


