2.37 вОХSQL - SQL Database Interface
==================================

вОХSQL was kindly contributed by Elias M√•rtenson.

   As of GNU APL 1.6, the native function SQL has been replaced by the
system function вОХSQL, described below.  вОХSQL has an axis argument that
selects a sub-function of вОХSQL.

2.37.1 вОХSQL[0] : display subfunctions
-------------------------------------

      вОХSQL[0]''
Available function numbers:
type  вОХSQL[1] file      - open a database file, return reference ID for it
      вОХSQL[2] ref       - close database
query вОХSQL[3,db] params - send SQL query
query вОХSQL[4,db] params - send SQL update
      вОХSQL[5] ref       - begin a transaction
      вОХSQL[6] ref       - commit current transaction
      вОХSQL[7] ref       - rollback current transaction
      вОХSQL[8] ref       - list tables
ref   вОХSQL[9] table     - list columns for table
      вОХSQL[10] type     - return the library version number
      вОХSQL[11] type     - return the library version string

2.37.2 ref вЖР A вОХSQL[1] B : open database
----------------------------------------

      type  вОХSQL[1] file

   Connect to database of type A using connection arguments B. The
result is a database handle ref to be used in the other вОХSQL functions.

   A must be a string indicating the database type.  Currently supported
values are вАЩpostgresqlвАЩ and вАЩsqliteвАЩ.

   B is the connection parameters which depends on the type of database:

   - For typeвЙ°вАЩsqliteвАЩ: the argument is string pointing to the database
file.

   - For typeвЙ°вАЩpostgresqlвАЩ, the argument is a standard connect string as
described in the PostgreSQL documentation.

   This function returns a database handle that should be used when
using other SQL functions.  This value should be seen as an opaque
handle.  It is, however, guaranteed that the handle is a scalar value.

2.37.3 вОХSQL[2] B : close database
---------------------------------

      вОХSQL[2] ref

   Disconnect from database ref.

   B is the database handle that should be disconnected.  After this
function has been called, no further operations are to be performed on
this handle.  Future calls to вОХSQL[1] may reuse previously disconnected
handles.

2.37.4 Z вЖР A вОХSQL[3, ref] B : database query (with result)
----------------------------------------------------------

      query вОХSQL[3, ref] params

   Execute a select statement and return the result table.

   The axis parameter indicates the database handle.

   A is a select statement to be executed.  Positional parameters can be
supplied by specifying a question mark "?"  in the statement.

   B is an array containing the values for the positional parameters.
If the array is of rank 2, the statement will be executed multiple times
with each row being the values for each call.

   The return value Z is a rank-2 array representing the result of the
select statement.  Null values are returned as вНђ and empty strings are
returned as вАЭ.

2.37.5 Z вЖР A вОХSQL[4, ref] B : database query (w/o result)
---------------------------------------------------------

      query вОХSQL[4, ref] params

   Execute an SQL statement that does not return a result.

   This function is identical to SQLвИЖSelect with the exception that it
is used on statements which do not return a result table.

2.37.6 вОХSQL[5] B : start transaction
------------------------------------

      вОХSQL[5] ref

   Begin a transaction.

2.37.7 вОХSQL[6] B : commit transaction
-------------------------------------

      вОХSQL[6] ref

   Commit a transaction.

2.37.8 вОХSQL[7] B : rollback transaction
---------------------------------------

      вОХSQL[7] ref

   Rolls back the current transaction.

2.37.9 ZвЖРвОХSQL[8] B : table names
--------------------------------

      вОХSQL[8] ref

   Return an array containing the name of all tables.

2.37.10 ZвЖРвОХSQL[9] B : column names
----------------------------------

      ref  вОХSQL[9] table

   Return an array containing information about the columns in the given
table.  Currently, the column layout is as follows:

   Name Type

   More columns containing additional information may be added in a
future release.

2.37.11 Z вЖР вОХSQL[10] B : library version number
-----------------------------------------------

Return the version number (integer scalar) of the library that was used
to implement the database type B.

2.37.12 Z вЖР вОХSQL[11] B : library version string
-----------------------------------------------

Return the version string of the library that was used to implement the
database type B.


