2.40.6 XML Queries
------------------

The different functions in dyadic вОХXML are intended to construct XML
queries.  An XML query extracts information from, or modifies
information in, an XML document.  XML queries may differ considerably in
their details, but usually follow these top-level steps:

  1. Read an XML document into, say, APL (APLвЖР0 вОХXML B or APLвЖР1 вОХXML B)
  2. Optionally, display the structure of the document (3, 4, or 5 вОХXML
     APL)
  3. Select a subset of XML nodes (= GNU APL member names, 6 вОХXML APL)
  4. retrieve or modify the data in the selected XML nodes (with
     something like MEMBERSвЖР(вКВAPL) FUN¬®6вОХXML APLвЖРвОХXML followed by
     MEMBERвКГ )
  5. Optionally, convert the modified XML document back to XML (0 вОХXML
     APL)


