5 Project Structure
*******************

The top-level directory of the GNU APL project has a structure like
this:

    apl-1.9/
    вФЬвФАвФА autom4te.cache
    вФЬвФАвФА build
    вФЬвФАвФА debian
    вФЬвФАвФА debian_tmp
    вФЬвФАвФА devel_doc
    вФЬвФАвФА doc
    вФЬвФАвФА erlang
    вФЬвФАвФА gnu-apl.d
    вФЬвФАвФА HOWTOs
    вФЬвФАвФА html
    вФЬвФАвФА m4
    вФЬвФАвФА rpm
    вФЬвФАвФА src
    вФЬвФАвФА support-files
    вФЬвФАвФА tools
    вФЬвФАвФА websock
    вФЬвФАвФА workspaces
    вФЬвФАвФА wslib2
    вФЬвФАвФА wslib3
    вФЬвФАвФА wslib4
    вФФвФАвФА wslib5

   Most of these directories are contained in the project tar file (e.g.
apl-1.9.tar.gz) and some are created during the build of GNU APL. Only
the directories in the top-level are shown above.

   The GNU APL project follows the standard layout for autoconf/automake
projects.  The top-level itself contains the files needed by
autoconf/automake and a handful of README-XXX files that might be of
interest when building GNU APL.

   The subdirectories are (in order of decreasing relevance):

* Menu:

* Section 5.1:: The subdirectory src
* Section 5.2:: The subdirectory support-files
* Section 5.3:: The subdirectory doc
* Section 5.4:: The subdirectory HOWTOs
* Section 5.5:: The subdirectories workspaces and wslib2 ... wslib5
* Section 5.6:: The subdirectory m4
* Section 5.7:: The subdirectories rpm, debian, and debian_tmp
* Section 5.8:: The subdirectory tools


